  "text": "While expression of the transgene was high in liver it was not absolutely liver specific. Low levels of transgene transcripts and, particularly, transgene-encoded ERCC1 protein (<5% of the level in liver) were observed in other tissues (particularly brain and testes) in some of the animals tested. This was not unexpected given previous reports of low levels of ectopic transgene expression from the same TTR promoter fragment [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
